title: Google\Cloud\ErrorReporting\V1beta1\ListGroupStatsRequest
name: ListGroupStatsRequest
description:
Specifies a set of ErrorGroupStats to return.

Generated from protobuf message google.devtools.clouderrorreporting.v1beta1.ListGroupStatsRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.project_name
params.description: Required. The resource name of the Google Cloud Platform project. Written as projects/{projectID} or projects/{projectNumber}, where {projectID} and {projectNumber} can be found in the Google Cloud Console. Examples: projects/my-project-123, projects/5551234.

params.name: data.group_id
params.description: Optional. List all ErrorGroupStats with these IDs.

params.name: data.service_filter
params.description: Optional. List only ErrorGroupStats which belong to a service context that matches the filter. Data for all service contexts is returned if this field is not specified.

params.name: data.time_range
params.description: Optional. List data for the given time range. If not set, a default time range is used. The field time_range_begin in the response will specify the beginning of this time range. Only ErrorGroupStats with a non-zero count in the given time range are returned, unless the request contains an explicit group_id list. If a group_id list is given, also ErrorGroupStats with zero occurrences are returned.

params.name: data.timed_count_duration
params.description: Optional. The preferred duration for a single returned TimedCount. If not set, no timed counts are returned.

params.name: data.alignment
params.description: Optional. The alignment of the timed counts to be returned. Default is ALIGNMENT_EQUAL_AT_END.

params.name: data.alignment_time
params.description: Optional. Time where the timed counts shall be aligned if rounded alignment is chosen. Default is 00:00 UTC.

params.name: data.order
params.description: Optional. The sort order in which the results are returned. Default is COUNT_DESC.

params.name: data.page_size
params.description: Optional. The maximum number of results to return per response. Default is 20.

params.name: data.page_token
params.description: Optional. A next_page_token provided by a previous response. To view additional results, pass this token along with the identical query parameters as the first request.
